ited Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"William","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Probably the most successful of all the Old French names of Germanic origin that were introduced to England by the Normans. It is derived from Germanic <i>wil</i> ‘will, desire’ + <i>helm</i> ‘helmet, protection’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"William DeTregirla was born in 1301, in England, United Kingdom. He married Jane Beckwith in England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter. He died after 1336, in his hometown."},"et":{"1301–aft 1336":"1301–pärast 1336","1302–1378":"1302–1378","1321–1352":"1321–1352","1301–1336":"1301–1336","1336":"1336","1302":"1302","1301":"1301","1378":"1378","1321":"1321","1352":"1352","aft 1336":"pärast 1336","Tregirls, Cornwall, Englad":"Cornwall, England","England":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1301–aft 1336":"1301–1336 jälkeen","1302–1378":"1302–1378","1321–1352":"1321–1352","1301–1336":"1301–1336","1336":"1336","1302":"1302","1301":"1301","1378":"1378","1321":"1321","1352":"1352","aft 1336":"1336 jälkeen","Tregirls, Cornwall, Englad":"Cornwall, England","England":"Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1301–aft 1336":"1301–après 1336","1302–1378":"1302–1378","1321–1352":"1321–1352","1301–1336":"1301–1336","1336":"1336","1302":"1302","1301":"1301","1378":"1378","1321":"1321","1352":"1352","aft 1336":"après 1336","Tregirls, Cornwall, Englad":"Cornouailles, Angleterre","England":"Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"William DeTregirla est